nce for needing additional setup. There’s a POM comment stating modules aren’t in doxia core anymore, so dependencies must be specified for proper component descriptor use.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating dependency options**\\n\\nI see the generated scaffold could use the xhtml5 compile dependency or utilize copyResources and createDocumentContext without needing external modules. This could extend meaningful coverage for the site renderer without the extra APT module, leveraging copyResources and model methods. However, the existing PR failed due to API changes rather than missing dependencies. I need to investigate the dependency graph, as doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 exposes SiteRenderingContext setters and getters, which include the maven artifact type.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YtZ0jMnpX89DQPniGT9oA2gG|fc_0be56e4e92dbc717016a3f4544633081938abae59976b54ecb", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "./gradlew -q dependencyInsight --configuration testRuntimeClasspath --dependency org.apache.maven:maven-artifact -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-site-renderer:1.9.1", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6938, "output": 768, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26138, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782531386121, "responseId": "resp_0be56e4e92dbc717016a3f453a92548193a0b029809ef2879d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_YtZ0jMnpX89DQPniGT9oA2gG|fc_0be56e4e92dbc717016a3f4544633081938abae59976b54ecb", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\nFAILURE: Build failed with an exception.\n\n* What went wrong:\nconfiguration 'testRuntimeClasspath' not found in configuration container for root project 'reachability-metadata'.\n\n* Try:\n> Run with --stacktrace option to get the stack trace.\n> Run with --info or --d